efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(32 * n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW 
explanation: The solution iterates through numbers, calculating the price based on set bits at positions x, 2x, 3x, etc. It continues until the accumulated price exceeds k. The algorithm's time complexity is dominated by the loop iterating through bit positions (32) for each number. The space complexity is constant as it uses a fixed amount of memory regardless of the input size.

